# SEO & PWA

## Document titles

Public pages: titles resolved via `usePublicDocumentTitle(pathname)` in `Layout`. Admin pages: `useAdminDocumentTitle(pathname)` in `AdminLayout`.

When adding a new route, add an entry to the appropriate map in `src/hooks/useDocumentTitle.ts`:

```tsx
"/new-slug": pageTitle("Page Name"),           // public
"/admin/new-slug": adminPageTitle("Page Name"), // admin
```

## Meta descriptions

Public meta comes from `useSeoSettings()` → `seo.pagesMeta[path]`. Per-page overrides are managed in Admin SEO (`/admin/seo`).

## PWA manifest

Configured in `vite.config.ts` via `vite-plugin-pwa`:

- `theme_color` and `background_color`: `#0D0E12` (matches `brand-bg`)
- Icons: `public/icons/pwa-192x192.png`, `pwa-512x512.png`, `apple-touch-icon.png`
- `lang`: `vi`, `start_url`: `/`

Do not change theme colors to raw hex outside design tokens when updating manifest.

## Site config

Global site name/description: `src/config/site.ts`. SEO settings persisted via `useSiteSettings()`.
